  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CSGFrame
    This frame has a GameMap, which the frame is able to load in or save.
    Draw
    Classes which inherit this class can draw on a MyCanvas.
    DrawButtonListener
    The class responsible for the change of different brushes when a button is clicked.
    EditorCanvas
    This is the canvas for the editor.
    EditorCanvasDraw
    This canvas makes up the editable map portion of the editor frame.
    EditorChaliceDraw
    This functions as a brush which edits the game map.
    EditorEmptyTileDraw
    Draws "empty tiles" on the canvas.
    EditorEnemySpawnerDraw
    Draws "enemy spawners" on the canvas.
    EditorFrame
    The user can edit, modify game maps.
    EditorGroundTileDraw
    Draws "ground tiles" on the canvas.
    EditorPlayerSpawnDraw
    Draws "player spawns" on the canvas.
    GameCanvas
    This is the canvas to display the game elements and state of the game.
    GameCanvasDraw  
    GameFrame  
    MouseListenerDelegator
    Helper class for easy change of Draws in MyCanvas.
    MyCanvas
    A Canvas supporting 2 layers: bottom for permanent, top for temporary draws.
    PlayerInputListener
    This key listener takes input from the keyboard from the user, then does some thing to the player character according to the input.
    PlayerMouseListener
    This mouse listener will handle the mouse input from the user and has effect on the player's actions.
    SaveLoadButtonListener
    Saves current progress from the canvas onto a file or Loads in up a file to continue where the user left off.
    SelectionFrame
    Lets the user choose between two (2) very important things.
